1. Create a folder on your desktop called 'mern-crash-course'.  Inside of that folder, create folders called 'frontend' and 'backend'.  We will focus on the backend first and build an API.
   Once we build it, we will move on to the frontend.

2. Ensure that you are inside of the 'mern-crash-course' folder, and initialize/set up a new npm package.

3. Install the following packages: express, mongoose, dotenv
